<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 5:45PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
Wilkes County through 615 PM EDT...
At 545 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Boomer, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
North Wilkesboro...
Wilkesboro...
Ronda...
Boomer...
Mc Grady...
Windy Gap...
and Mulberry.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
